name: Bryan Fury
data: The kickboxer and former cop Bryan Fury is a staple of the Tekken franchise, being introduced back in Tekken 3 as a replacement to the Muay Thai fighter Bruce Irwin. Since then he has had many iterations including a big rework to the character in Tekken 6. His signature taunt is by far the most powerful techroll catch in the entire game where just guessing wrong once can lead to Bryan getting a fully guaranteed launcher.

Being a counter hit focused character, Bryan is able to remain very safe while still throwing out moves with huge reward. Moves such as 3+4, 1+2, and his infamous Mach Kick (f,F+4) allow Bryan to control space incredibly well, and from many ranges. Bryan excels at fishing out counter hits and forcing the opponent to hold their guard. His whiff punishment is decent with Boa Crusher (f+4,1) being an excellent, long range, mid launcher and his Smash and Mach Kick (QCB+2,4) being whiff confirmable with incredible range and damage.

Bryan boasts possibly the best okizeme in the game, although it requires very high execution to get the most out of. Against a skilled Bryan, the opponent constantly has to think about their getup options as to avoid getting fully launched by the infamously difficult taunt to Jet Upper.
